<paragraph id="8B897E5CFFBDFF8D2AB26EF3FC3BFAE7" blockId="8.[151,1437,977,1318]" pageId="8" pageNumber="553">
<taxonomicName id="4C3605DFFFBDFF8D2AB26EF3FDB9FC2F" authority="Canepari, 1997" authorityName="Canepari" authorityYear="1997" box="[151,591,977,1003]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Platynaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nepalensis">
<emphasis id="B942A24EFFBDFF8D2AB26EF3FE6EFC2F" box="[151,408,977,1003]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="553">Platynaspis nepalensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFA703ADFFBDFF8D2B856EF3FDB9FC2F" author="Canepari, C." box="[416,591,977,1003]" pageId="8" pageNumber="553" pagination="1 - 65" refId="ref4576" refString="Canepari, C. (1997) Coccinellidae (Coleoptera) from the Nepal Himalayas. Stuttgarter Beitrage zur Naturkunde, Serie A (Biologie), 565 (65), 1 - 65." type="journal article" year="1997">Canepari, 1997</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, described from 
<collectingCountry id="F3213ECCFFBDFF8D29296EF3FCA4FC2F" box="[780,850,977,1003]" name="Nepal" pageId="8" pageNumber="553">Nepal</collectingCountry>
, is transferred to 
<taxonomicName id="4C3605DFFFBDFF8D2E3D6EF3FB7CFC2F" authorityName="Weise" authorityYear="1901" box="[1048,1162,977,1003]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Horniolus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B942A24EFFBDFF8D2E3D6EF3FB7CFC2F" box="[1048,1162,977,1003]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="553">Horniolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Canepariâ€™s illustrations and the images of the 
<typeStatus id="548DC0FEFFBDFF8D2BB36ED6FE0EFBCA" box="[406,504,1012,1038]" pageId="8" pageNumber="553">holotype</typeStatus>
female (obtained through the courtesy of Dr. Giulio Cuccodoro, MHNG) (
<figureCitation id="130D62D9FFBDFF8D2F6A6ED6FA65FBCB" box="[1359,1427,1012,1039]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1287,1311]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,182,1260]" captionTargetId="figure-15@9.[151,1435,181,1263]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5. Horniolus nepalensis (Canepari): a. holotype female (MHNG), dorsal view; b. holotype labels; c. holotype female, abdomen; d. female genitalia, glued to card (Image credit: Giulio Cuccodoro, MHNG)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6332191" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6332191/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="553">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
) clearly establish it as a species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3605DFFFBDFF8D28396935FD78FBF5" authorityName="Weise" authorityYear="1901" box="[540,654,1047,1073]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Horniolus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B942A24EFFBDFF8D28396935FD78FBF5" box="[540,654,1047,1073]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="553">Horniolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The dorsal habitus (
<figureCitation id="130D62D9FFBDFF8D295B6935FC26FBF5" box="[894,976,1046,1073]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1287,1311]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,182,1260]" captionTargetId="figure-15@9.[151,1435,181,1263]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5. Horniolus nepalensis (Canepari): a. holotype female (MHNG), dorsal view; b. holotype labels; c. holotype female, abdomen; d. female genitalia, glued to card (Image credit: Giulio Cuccodoro, MHNG)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6332191" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6332191/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="553">Fig. 5a</figureCitation>
) of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3605DFFFBDFF8D2E256935FB65FBF5" authorityName="Canepari" authorityYear="1997" box="[1024,1171,1047,1073]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Platynaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nepalensis">
<emphasis id="B942A24EFFBDFF8D2E256935FB65FBF5" box="[1024,1171,1047,1073]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="553">P. nepalensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is reminiscent of some of the known species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3605DFFFBDFF8D2B9D691BFDDCFB97" authorityName="Weise" authorityYear="1901" box="[440,554,1081,1107]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Horniolus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B942A24EFFBDFF8D2B9D691BFDDCFB97" box="[440,554,1081,1107]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="553">Horniolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
such as 
<taxonomicName id="4C3605DFFFBDFF8D28B66918FCC7FB97" authorityName=": Canepari" authorityYear="2003" box="[659,817,1081,1107]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Horniolus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hisamatsui">
<emphasis id="B942A24EFFBDFF8D28B66918FCC7FB97" box="[659,817,1081,1107]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="553">H. hisamatsui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C3605DFFFBDFF8D294B6918FBCFFB97" authorityName="Hoang" authorityYear="1979" box="[878,1081,1081,1107]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Horniolus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sonduongensis">
<emphasis id="B942A24EFFBDFF8D294B6918FBCFFB97" box="[878,1081,1081,1107]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="553">H. sonduongensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(as illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA703ADFFBDFF8D2F2B691BFEB6FBB2" author="Szawaryn, K. &amp; Vetrovec, J." pageId="8" pageNumber="553" pagination="573 - 580" refId="ref5715" refString="Szawaryn, K. &amp; Vetrovec, J. (2020) A new species of Horniolus Weise with remarks on the systematic position of the genus (Coleoptera: Coccinellidae). Zootaxa, 4861 (4), 573 - 580. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4861.4.5" type="journal article" year="2020">Szawaryn &amp; VÄ›trovec 2020</bibRefCitation>
) in having a discal black spot on each elytron. The abdominal postcoxal lines (
<figureCitation id="130D62D9FFBDFF8D2EE0697EFAE0FBB3" box="[1221,1302,1116,1143]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1287,1311]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,182,1260]" captionTargetId="figure-15@9.[151,1435,181,1263]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5. Horniolus nepalensis (Canepari): a. holotype female (MHNG), dorsal view; b. holotype labels; c. holotype female, abdomen; d. female genitalia, glued to card (Image credit: Giulio Cuccodoro, MHNG)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6332191" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6332191/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="553">Fig. 5c</figureCitation>
) are deeply semicircular and complete and typical of 
<emphasis id="B942A24EFFBDFF8D2855695DFD1FFB5D" box="[624,745,1151,1177]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="553">
<taxonomicName id="4C3605DFFFBDFF8D2855695DFD13FB5D" authorityName="Weise" authorityYear="1901" box="[624,741,1151,1177]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Horniolus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Horniolus</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
The female genitalia (
<figureCitation id="130D62D9FFBDFF8D29CE695DFBCBFB5D" box="[1003,1085,1150,1177]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1287,1311]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,182,1260]" captionTargetId="figure-15@9.[151,1435,181,1263]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5. Horniolus nepalensis (Canepari): a. holotype female (MHNG), dorsal view; b. holotype labels; c. holotype female, abdomen; d. female genitalia, glued to card (Image credit: Giulio Cuccodoro, MHNG)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6332191" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6332191/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="553">Fig. 5d</figureCitation>
) (illustrated in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA703ADFFBDFF8D2ECA695DFA6EFB5D" author="Canepari, C." box="[1263,1432,1151,1177]" pageId="8" pageNumber="553" pagination="1 - 65" refId="ref4576" refString="Canepari, C. (1997) Coccinellidae (Coleoptera) from the Nepal Himalayas. Stuttgarter Beitrage zur Naturkunde, Serie A (Biologie), 565 (65), 1 - 65." type="journal article" year="1997">Canepari 1997</bibRefCitation>
: p. 40, Figs 123â€“125) with intricately coiled spermatheca and the elongate triangular coxites are characteristic of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3605DFFFBDFF8D2AB269E6FEFFFB1A" authorityName="Weise" authorityYear="1901" box="[151,265,1220,1246]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Horniolus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B942A24EFFBDFF8D2AB269E6FEFFFB1A" box="[151,265,1220,1246]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="553">Horniolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and not found in any of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C3605DFFFBDFF8D286D69E6FD3DFB1A" authority="Redtenbacher, 1843" authorityName="Redtenbacher" authorityYear="1843" box="[584,715,1220,1246]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Platynaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B942A24EFFBDFF8D286D69E6FD3DFB1A" box="[584,715,1220,1246]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="553">Platynaspis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species of this region or elsewhere, all of which have broad and transverse coxites. Only 
<emphasis id="B942A24EFFBDFF8D2B8F69C5FDC5FAC5" box="[426,563,1255,1281]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="553">
<taxonomicName id="4C3605DFFFBDFF8D2B8F69C5FDD9FAC5" authorityName="Strohecker" authorityYear="1953" box="[426,559,1255,1281]" class="Insecta" family="Endomychidae" genus="Crypticolus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Crypticolus</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
a genus of Platynaspini from 
<collectingCountry id="F3213ECCFFBDFF8D295B69C5FBF1FAC5" box="[894,1031,1255,1281]" name="Madagascar" pageId="8" pageNumber="553">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
, has elongate triangular coxites with a complex, distally coiled spermatheca (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA703ADFFBDFF8D287D6829FC34FAE7" author="Slipinski, A. &amp; Tomaszewska, W." box="[600,962,1289,1318]" pageId="8" pageNumber="553" pagination="493 - 497" refId="ref5629" refString="Slipinski, A. &amp; Tomaszewska, W. (2002) The genus Crypticolus Strohecker - redescription and transfer from Endomychidae to Coccinellidae (Coleoptera, Cucujoidea). Annales Zoologici, 52 (4), 493 - 497." type="journal article" year="2002">ÅšlipiÅ„ski &amp; Tomaszewska 2002</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
